  "text": "While these cases account for only 24% of the observations, longer maturities could be indicative of differences in drawdown patterns. The Collaterlized i variable is equal to one if the credit line is collateralized, which was found to be significant in [CITATION_1] as well as [CITATION_2] . Eleven percent of the observations correspond to collateralized lines.",
